

About this archive.
===================

This archive includes a few files to show the simplicity of localising
your source using FlexCat. The example is given in E, but the principles
apply to any other language.


Included in this archive:

AllHelloLocalWorld.e                       Example for those without EPP
HelloLocalWorld.e                          Example for those with EPP

HelloLocalWorld                            The precompiled executable

catalogs/HelloLocalWorld.cd                The English Catalogue description
catalogs/HelloLocalWorld.ct                An empty catalogue translation

catalogs/français/HelloLocalWorld.ct       The french .ct
catalogs/français/HelloLocalWorld.catalog  The compiled locale .catalog

pmodules/HelloLocalWorld_cat               The FlexCat generated EPP source


Only HelloLocalWorld.e and HelloLocalWorld.cd had to be written.
Everything else is a result of either FlexCat or EC (via EPP). As you can
see the work required to produce localised code is virtually none!



About FlexCat
-------------

FlexCat is an extemely powerful .catalog and source generator for the
programmer of /any/ language E, C, Assm, etc.

The main purpose of the program is to generate *all* the source required
to include localisation in your program, leaving you free to worry about
the program itself. You need know */nothing/* about the locale.library,
since all those calls are dealt with by the generated source.

Amazingly, FlexCat is so flexible, it can even generate localised source
for machines without the locale.library! It does this by using the
iffparse.library instead.

Because the source is generated from an ascii .sd (source description)
file, FlexCat can generate source for practically any language. .sd files
are included for C, E, AztecAssembler & Oberon.



