Programming
-----------

From a programmers point of view, things are just as easy.

Basically you produce your .CD file, which contains the strings  in the
default language (usually English), and referances to those strings.

In place of the strings within the program, you use the 
"get_xxx_string(ref)" routine, with the desired string reference as an
argument.

Next you run the source and the .cd through FlexCat.

flexcat then generates a sourcefile containing the get_xxx_string()
procedure, and those for opening and closing the locale.library.

These are placed in the xxx_cat PModule. This E source can be inserted
in the main program if desired, or linked at compile time with EPP.

In addition, FlexCat will generate empty .ct (catalog translation) files,
ready for "foreignisation" ;-), and will compile the the translated .cts
into language/???.catalog files.


